                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24074/9</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Calhoun</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Calhoun refers to legation’s April 22, and says vice consul general at Hankow
                    reports Hunan quiet; says there were no disturbances last week; and that most of
                    the missionaries have left Province.</p>
            </div>
